cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with pattern matching algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves analysis of the complexity of algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper provides a provable separation in complexity between exact pattern matching and pattern matching with wildcards. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper involves analysis of the average-case complexity. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) may be relevant as pattern matching is a common problem in computational geometry.
